article.headline: Dayton 81, Wofford 64
article.story: DAYTON, Ohio (AP) -- Ramod Marshall scored 10 of his 15 points during a 21-0 run to rally Dayton to an 81-64 victory over Wofford on Monday night. Sean Finn had 12 points and Keith Waleskowski and Monty Scott each had 11 for the Flyers (10-1). Greg Taylor led Wofford (3-7) with 13. Howard Wilkerson added 12 and Sam Daniels 10. Dayton outrebounded Wofford 46-21, led by Waleskowski with 11 and Finn with 10. The Flyers, whose only loss was to unbeaten No. 12 Cincinnati, struggled early and trailed 22-16 with 8:43 remaining in the first half. But Marshall started the key run with a layup and a 3-pointer, and Wofford went scoreless for nearly eight minutes as Dayton built its lead to 39-25 at halftime. Wofford started the second half with a 10-2 run to get within six but could not sustain the effort, and Dayton led most of the second half by double digits.
